text: {| |} RFA Wave Master (A193) was a Wave-class fleet support tanker of the Royal Fleet Auxiliary. She was built as Empire Salisbury by Sir J. Laing & Sons Ltd, and transferred to the Royal Fleet Auxiliary in 1946. She was laid up at Singapore on 23 September 1962, and scrapped at Jurong in May 1963. ==References== Category:Wave-class oilers Category:Tankers of the Royal Fleet Auxiliary Category:Ministry of War Transport ships Category:World War II merchant ships of the United Kingdom Category:1944 ships
